    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.15.29-30_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">29</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Buffalo</figDesc>
                        <p>DEPARTMENT OF THE INTERIOR</p>
                    </figure>
                
                    <hi rend="caps">THE SECRETARY OF THE INTERIOR
                        <lb/>
                    WASHINGTON</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>MAY - 1 1931</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                    
                            <addrLine>Branson, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am in receipt of your letter of April 24 asking for permission to visit the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation for the purpose of gathering material bearing upon the history of the Sioux.</p>
                
                <p>There appears to be no reason why you should not be allowed to make the proposed trip, and we feel sure that Mr. Courtright, Field Agent in charge, will extend to you such courtesy as is consistent with his official duties.</p> 
                
                <p>We would like to have a short report of your meetings with these Indians.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <unclear/>
                    Secretary.
                </closer>
                
                <note place="right margin"><unclear reason="missing"/><hi rend="caps">AFFAIRS</hi> <unclear reason="missing"/>May - 6 1931</note>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.15.29-30_002"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">30</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">
                        CLASS OF SERVICE DESIRED
                        DOMESTIC     CABLE
                        TELEGRAM     FULL RATE
                        DAY LETTER   DEFERRED
                        NIGHT        CABLE
                           MESSAGE      LETTER
                        NIGHT   X    WEEK END
                           LETTER       LETTER
                    </hi>
                    Patrons should check class of service desired: otherwise messages will be transmitted as a full rate communication.
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">
                        WESTERN
                            <lb/>
                        UNION
                            <lb/>
                        NECOMB CARLTON, PRESIDENT           J.C. WILLEVER, FIRST VICE-PRESIDENT
                    </hi>
                    
                        Form 1206-<hi rend="caps">A
                        
                        NO.  CASH OR CHG.
                        
                        CHECK
                        
                        TIME FILED
                    </hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="italic">Send the following message, subject to the terms on back hereof, which are hereby agreed to</hi>
                </fw>
                    
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Washington, <hi rend="caps">D. C.</hi>
                        May 8, 1931,
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">B.G.</hi> Courtright, Supt.</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Pine Ridge Agency,</addrLine>
                                <addrLine>Pine Ridge, South Dakota,</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </opener>
                <p>If John Neihardt of St. Louis is at Pine Ridge I commend him to your favorable attention. He desires to meet your old Sioux warriors get material for epic poem on ghost dance. He is all right. Am writing you today.</p>
                <closer>
                Malcom McDowell, Secretary,
                Board of Indian Commissioners,
                </closer>
                
                <note>Charge to
                Malcom McDowell
                account.</note>
                
            </div1>
